Merge sort
Merge sort Big O

Merge Sort is a stable, divide-and-conquer algorithm that guarantees \(O(n\log n)\) time complexity 
in all cases. It works by recursively splitting the array in half until each subarray has only one element, 
then merging those subarrays back together in sorted order

Leet program
the merge method takes in another LinkedList as an input and merges it with current linkedlist.
The elements in both lists are assumed to be in ascending order, but the input lists themselves do no need to be sorted.


